I didnt like the stock and looked for months for an original wood stock for this model rifle... and paid through the nose for it... it looks better than with the Dragonov aftermarket and it's correct. title: For Sale:  MAK90 "Sporter"
postcontent: I bought this rifle in California & have had a lot of fun with it.  I have done mostly bench shooting.The original stock cracked, so I have changed over enough parts to "made in USA" to be compliant.As you can see by the picture, obvious changes are adjustable stock, houge grip (very nice), eotech (and doubler with quick release mount; the doubler can swing to the side as well) and pibod.Less obvious is adjustable trigger (Currently adjusted to a lighter pull, very little over travel that quickly resets.  I have not had any double fires since changing to this trigger).   It has an enanced mag release & safety lever -- good for range shooting, as you can lock the slide back in safe mode. The muzle brake is a pin on variety and has remained solid for many years.The *only* reason I'm selling it is that I'm moving back to California, and they don't like this rifle anymore.Included with the rifle is a bunch of ammo (just under 900 rounds), including a sealed spam can of non corrosive russian ammo; several metal/chinese mags; 2 30 and 2 20 round tapco magazines.  (the 20 rounders are nice to shoot from bipod on bench).  All 4 tapco mags have weapontech follwers) Metal (chinese) mags are mostly rust free (very minor rust on one mag); the mags that are bolted together have weapontech followers; the lone 30 & 10 round have the old tapco followers. The end result is you get to count the metal mags as 1 922r compliance part. (every little bit helps)There is also a peep site on the rear and wire "+" site on the front; but I mostly used the eotech.  (NOTE: The eotech needs to be re-adjusted as it was moved from another rifle to this one when the original was stolen).

The PASGT Vest is a front opening design which protects the upper torso of the body. The ballistic filler consists of 13 plies of 14 oz/yd2 (457g/m2) water repellent treated Aramid Kevlar 29 fabric. The inner and outer cover, shoulder pads and front closure flap of the vest are water repellent treated 8oz/yd2 (271 g/m2) ballistic nylon cloth. The outer cover is woodland camouflage printed and the inner cover is olive green. The vest has a 3/4 collar, pivoting shoulder pads, two front pockets, two grenade hangers and rifle butt patches at the front shoulder area. The front flap and pocket flaps have hook and loop fastener tape closures. The side overlaps are made flexible through the use of 1-1/2 inch (3.8cm) wide elastic webbing.The PASGT Vest has an increased ability over the now obsolete nylon vest to stop or slow down fragments; it will reduce the number of wounds, especially serious and lethal; from exploding conventional and improved conventional munitions.
